<subSubSection id="C314657C921BE75DA1E6FD2AA7636AA3" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB136F7921BE75DA1E6FD2AA4266DAF" blockId="2.[151,583,654,717]" box="[151,274,691,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
(
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA1EEFD2AA43D6DAF" box="[159,265,691,717]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–6" captionStart-1="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId-0="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox-0="[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetBox-1="[170,1436,181,1465]" captionTargetId-0="figure-21@3.[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetId-1="figure-32@4.[151,1436,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–6. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, male holotype deposited in SDEI. 1–3, scale bar 5 mm; 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4 &amp; 5, head; 4, dorsal view; 5, lateral view; 6, labels." captionText-1="FIGURES 7–9. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, non-type female specimen from Honduras, scale bars 2 mm. 7, dorsal view; 8, ventral view; 9, lateral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673939" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673941" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4673939/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4673941/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Figs. 1–9</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136F7921BE75DA1E6FD63A7636AA3" blockId="2.[151,1437,762,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE5921BE75DA1E6FD63A48F6C77" bold="true" box="[151,443,762,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Morphological remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D74921BE75DA0B5FD62A7986C77" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1914" box="[452,684,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculata">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE5921BE75DA0B5FD62A7986C77" box="[452,684,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Rhiginia bimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a moderately sized species (
<quantity id="4CF69B12921BE75DA560FD63A1A46C77" box="[1041,1168,762,789]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" unit="mm" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16 mm</quantity>
), and the images of the male 
<typeStatus id="54B58855921BE75DA1A9FC86A40E6C5B" box="[216,314,799,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">holotype</typeStatus>
presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B06921BE75DA091FC86A78E6C5B" author="Gil-Santana, H. R." box="[480,698,799,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" pagination="502 - 520" refId="ref22934" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. (2019) New records, taxonomic notes, and the description of a new species of Reduviidae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from Ecuador. Zootaxa, 4613 (3), 502 - 520. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4613.3.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Gil-Santana (2019)</bibRefCitation>
(wrongly labeled as female 
<typeStatus id="54B58855921BE75DA579FC86A15E6C5B" box="[1032,1130,799,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">holotype</typeStatus>
in his 
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA5CEFC86A0306C5B" box="[1215,1284,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, male holotype deposited in SDEI. 1–3, scale bar 5 mm; 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4 &amp; 5, head; 4, dorsal view; 5, lateral view; 6, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
caption) and provided by SDEI for the present study (
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA315FCDAA7FA6C3C" box="[612,718,835,862]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, male holotype deposited in SDEI. 1–3, scale bar 5 mm; 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4 &amp; 5, head; 4, dorsal view; 5, lateral view; 6, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Figs. 1–6</figureCitation>
) match 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B06921BE75DA25AFCDAA6DE6C3F" author="Breddin, G." box="[811,1002,835,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" pagination="53 - 59" refId="ref22142" refString="Breddin, G. (1914) Neue oder wenig gekannte neotropische Hemiptera. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 36, 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1914">Breddin’s (1914)</bibRefCitation>
description of the color: the specimen is largely dark brown to black, with the dorsum of the head, pronotum (except two small paramedial and two lateral black spots on the transverse sulcus), and base of the corium orangish. The connexivum also has a very narrow yellow to orange margin on the dorsal surface, but it is entirely yellow to orange on the ventral surface. It is unclear to what extent this color pattern may vary. The head appears somewhat subrectangular, with a very elevated clypeus somewhat rounded at the median portion and a slightly convex frons in lateral view. The ocelli are separated from one another by a little more than the diameter of an ocellus and occupy half to two-thirds of the ocellar tubercle in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA08AFBA6A7B06B3B" box="[507,644,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, male holotype deposited in SDEI. 1–3, scale bar 5 mm; 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4 &amp; 5, head; 4, dorsal view; 5, lateral view; 6, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Figs. 1, 3–4</figureCitation>
). The pronotum has a medially concaved anterior margin and rounded, almost indiscernible, anterolateral protuberances. The anterior lobe is approximately half the length of the posterior lobe, the medial longitudinal sulcus is very shallow near the anterior margin, and the transverse sulcus lacks deep paramedial punctations (
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA0DDFB32A4DA6BA7" box="[428,494,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, male holotype deposited in SDEI. 1–3, scale bar 5 mm; 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4 &amp; 5, head; 4, dorsal view; 5, lateral view; 6, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Additionally, the hemelytra (
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA238FB32A6BE6BA7" box="[841,906,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, male holotype deposited in SDEI. 1–3, scale bar 5 mm; 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4 &amp; 5, head; 4, dorsal view; 5, lateral view; 6, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) ends just before the apex of the abdomen, the inner discal cell (Cu+1A cell) in the membrane is subrectangular, and the proximal margin of the Cu+1A membranal cell is about twice that of the outer discal membranal cell (M+Cu cell). Abdominal sternite II has longitudinal ridges medially (
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA079FA8EA4786A53" box="[264,332,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[191,1396,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, male holotype deposited in SDEI. 1–3, scale bar 5 mm; 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4 &amp; 5, head; 4, dorsal view; 5, lateral view; 6, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). The coloration in the female (
<figureCitation id="13352A72921BE75DA3D9FA8EA6266A53" box="[680,786,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox="[170,1436,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-32@4.[151,1436,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–9. Rhiginia bimaculata Breddin, 1914, non-type female specimen from Honduras, scale bars 2 mm. 7, dorsal view; 8, ventral view; 9, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673941/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Figs. 7–9</figureCitation>
) is similar to the male 
<typeStatus id="54B58855921BE75DA57FFA8EA1406A53" box="[1038,1140,1303,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">holotype</typeStatus>
. In the female, the anterior pronotal lobe is subequal in length to the posterior lobe, and the hemelytra do not surpass the anterior margin of tergite VII. Additionally, the female appears to have a more ovate or globular head, strongly convex frons above the eyes, slightly elevated clypeus, and smaller ocelli that are separated by more than the diameter of an ocellus and that occupy less area on the ocellar tubercle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314657C921BE75DA1B6FA53A70A6867" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB136F7921BE75DA1B6FA53A70A6867" blockId="2.[151,1437,762,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE5921BE75DA1B6FA53A4786A86" bold="true" box="[199,332,1482,1508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B06921BE75DA020FA52A73A6A87" author="Breddin, G." box="[337,526,1483,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" pagination="53 - 59" refId="ref22142" refString="Breddin, G. (1914) Neue oder wenig gekannte neotropische Hemiptera. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 36, 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1914">Breddin’s (1914)</bibRefCitation>
short original description is dominated with information on color patterns, appears to be based on a single male specimen, lacks illustrations, and includes very little information on structural characters. After 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B06921BE75DA1ADF98AA4A9694F" author="Breddin, G." box="[220,413,1555,1581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" pagination="53 - 59" refId="ref22142" refString="Breddin, G. (1914) Neue oder wenig gekannte neotropische Hemiptera. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 36, 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1914">Breddin’s (1914)</bibRefCitation>
description, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D74921BE75DA342F98AA7E7694F" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1914" box="[563,723,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculata">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE5921BE75DA342F98AA7E7694F" box="[563,723,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">R. bimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was only cited in catalogs and checklists (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B06921BE75DA5B2F98AA0A5694F" author="Gil-Santana, H. R." box="[1219,1425,1555,1581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" pagination="502 - 520" refId="ref22934" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. (2019) New records, taxonomic notes, and the description of a new species of Reduviidae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from Ecuador. Zootaxa, 4613 (3), 502 - 520. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4613.3.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Gil-Santana 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B06921BE75DA1E6F9AEA4466933" author="Gil-Santana, H. R." box="[151,370,1591,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" pagination="502 - 520" refId="ref22934" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. (2019) New records, taxonomic notes, and the description of a new species of Reduviidae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from Ecuador. Zootaxa, 4613 (3), 502 - 520. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4613.3.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Gil-Santana (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, however, presented a photograph of the dorsal habitus of the male 
<typeStatus id="54B58855921BE75DA51EF9AEA1E56933" box="[1135,1233,1591,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D74921BE75DA586F9AEA0A16933" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1914" box="[1271,1429,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculata">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE5921BE75DA586F9AEA0A16933" box="[1271,1429,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">R. bimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the first figure presented of this species in the literature despite its large geographical distribution (
<collectingCountry id="F3197667921BE75DA46BF9C2A0AC6917" box="[1306,1432,1627,1653]" name="Guatemala" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3197667921BE75DA1E6F9E6A43369FB" box="[151,263,1663,1689]" name="Honduras" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Honduras</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3197667921BE75DA060F9E6A4BA69FB" box="[273,398,1663,1689]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3197667921BE75DA0E9F9E6A4C069FB" box="[408,500,1663,1689]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3197667921BE75DA08FF9E6A75B69FB" box="[510,623,1663,1689]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
